---
const items = [
	{
		q: 'Do I need both the plugin and the CLI?',
		a: 'No. The plugin includes the CLI under the hood. Install the plugin if you use Claude Code or Cursor; install the CLI on its own for direct integrations, scripting, or unsupported hosts.',
	},
	{
		q: 'Which path should I start with?',
		a: 'Plugin if you primarily code in Claude Code or Cursor. CLI if you want to wire Archcore into a custom host, CI, or another agent over MCP.',
	},
	{
		q: 'Which AI agents are supported?',
		a: 'Claude Code, Cursor, GitHub Copilot, Gemini CLI, Codex CLI, OpenCode, Roo Code, and Cline. Any agent that speaks MCP can read .archcore/.',
	},
	{
		q: 'What does Archcore write into my repo?',
		a: 'A .archcore/ directory of typed Markdown documents (decisions, rules, guides, plans, specs) and a sync manifest that stores relations between them. Everything is plain text and lives in git.',
	},
	{
		q: 'How do hooks and MCP work together?',
		a: 'MCP gives the agent on-demand access to typed documents and relations. Session hooks inject the right context at the right moment — e.g. before a file edit — so the agent does not have to ask.',
	},
	{
		q: 'Do I need any external services?',
		a: 'No. Archcore runs entirely from your repo. No accounts, no SaaS, no telemetry. The plugin and CLI are open source.',
	},
	{
		q: 'How is this different from CLAUDE.md or AGENTS.md?',
		a: 'Instruction files are flat memory the agent reads each turn. Archcore is a structured graph of typed documents the agent queries through MCP. Decisions, rules, specs, and workflows have their own document types and relate to each other.',
	},
	{
		q: 'How do I keep the CLI updated?',
		a: 'Use your package manager (npm, brew, scoop) or run archcore self-update. Releases are tracked in the changelog.',
	},
];
---

<section class="section faq">
	<div class="container-narrow faq__intro">
		<h2 class="faq__headline">Common questions.</h2>
	</div>

	<div class="container-narrow">
		<div class="faq__list">
			{items.map((item) => (
				<details class="faq-item">
					<summary class="faq-item__summary">
						<span class="faq-item__question">{item.q}</span>
						<span class="faq-item__chevron" aria-hidden="true">
							<svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="14" height="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
								<path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4" />
							</svg>
						</span>
					</summary>
					<div class="faq-item__answer">
						<p>{item.a}</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			))}
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.faq__intro {
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.faq__headline {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 28px;
		line-height: 1.08;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: -0.035em;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	@media (min-width: 50rem) {
		.faq__headline {
			font-size: 34px;
			line-height: 1.05;
		}
	}

	.faq__list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
	}

	.faq-item {
		border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
	}

	.faq-item:last-child {
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
	}

	.faq-item__summary {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 1rem;
		padding: 1rem 0;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
	}

	.faq-item__summary::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.faq-item__summary:hover {
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-surface-muted) 60%, transparent);
	}

	.faq-item__question {
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	.faq-item__chevron {
		flex-shrink: 0;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		transition: transform 0.2s ease;
	}

	.faq-item[open] .faq-item__chevron {
		transform: rotate(180deg);
	}

	.faq-item__answer {
		padding: 0 0 1rem;
	}

	.faq-item__answer p {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 14px;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: var(--color-text-secondary);
		max-width: 640px;
	}
</style>
